BFN 

  [Text] Dakar, 26 May (AFP) -- Abdoulaye Wade, the main 
Senegalese opposition leader, and his wife Viviane have been 
acquitted in the murder case involving the killing of 
Constitutional Council Vice President Babacar Seye on 15 May 
1993, the office of the director of public prosecution at the 
Dakar Appeal Court announced today. The appeal court also 
acquitted Ousmane Ngom and Abdoulaye Faye, two deputies of the 
Senegalese Democratic Party of which Abdoulaye Wade is the 
secretary general. All four were charged with "aiding and 
abetting murder" on 1 October 1993 but were released on bail. 

